TI  - Incidentally detected giant asymptomatic intercostal left lung hernia.
LID - e268166 [pii]
LID - 10.1136/bcr-2025-268166 [doi]
AB  - A man in his late 70s presented with venostatic symptoms and bilateral varicose 
      veins due to bilateral saphenofemoral junction incompetence. Systemic examination 
      revealed a left inframammary swelling that increased in size on inspiration and 
      decreased on expiration and was linked to an old chest wall trauma. Imaging 
      identified a giant intercostal lung herniation through the fractured ribs, which 
      was managed conservatively three decades ago. As he presently remains 
      asymptomatic for the lung herniation, he decided to continue with the 
      conservative management. The varicose veins were treated with endothermal 
      ablation, allowing him to resume routine activities.
