TI  - Cardiac injuries caused by trauma: Review and case reports.
PG  - 30-34
LID - S1752-928X(17)30127-0 [pii]
LID - 10.1016/j.jflm.2017.08.013 [doi]
AB  - Assessment of suspected cardiac injuries in a trauma setting is a challenging and 
      time-critical matter, with clinical and imaging findings having complementary 
      roles in the formation of an accurate diagnosis. In this article, we review the 
      supporting literature for the pathophysiology, classification and evaluation of 
      cardiac injuries caused by trauma. We also describe 4 cardiac trauma patients 
      seen at a tertiary referral hospital.
