TI  - Chronic heart perforation with 13.5 cm long Kirschner wire without pericardial 
      tamponade: an unusual sequelae after shoulder fracture.
PG  - 1895-7
AB  - We report a unique case of cardiac embolization with the Kirschner wire that has 
      been used for osteosynthesis for 24 months previously. According to the complete 
      analysis of medical records and autopsy report, the wire had migrated from the 
      right humeroscapular joint to the heart. Although migration of a Kirschner wire 
      has been reported in the literature, migration of the wire with a total length of 
      13.5 cm with no pericardial tamponade, despite myocardial perforation, has not 
      been previously described.
