DP  - 1992
TI  - [Diagnosis and treatment of complex closed chest injuries].
PG  - 47-9
AB  - The results of treatment of 256 patients with complicated closed chest injury are 
      discussed. Multiple fractures of the ribs were found in 178, closed pneumothorax 
      in 127, pneumohemothorax in 71, isolated hemothorax in 55, and rupture of the 
      diaphragm in 3 patients. Most patients received nonoperative treatment, 5 
      patients (6.1%) needed emergency thoracotomy. Early drainage of the pleural 
      cavity, endoscopic (thoracoscopy, bronchoscopy) methods of treatment, mechanical 
      stabilization of floating rib fractures made it possible to improve the results 
      and reduce the terms of treatment. Two (0.8%) persons died from shock and 
      cardiopulmonary insufficiency.
