DP  - 1991 Feb
TI  - [Significance of rib fractures in simple and multiple trauma].
PG  - 791-7
AB  - In a retrospect study we evaluated the clinical impact of traumatic rib 
      fractures. Our series included 96 patients treated between 1986 and 1988. 
      Haemato- and/or pneumothorax corresponded closely to the number of fractured 
      ribs. There was a highly significant association (p less than 0.001) between the 
      number of fractured ribs and polytrauma. The leading cause of injuries was a 
      traffic accident.
