VI  - 49
IP  - 6
DP  - 1990 Jun
TI  - Open fixation of flail chest after blunt trauma.
PG  - 993-5
AB  - Progressive left chest volume loss developed in a patient with severe flail chest 
      despite reasonable oxygenation without intubation. Because of this chest volume 
      loss, pain, and shortness of breath, she underwent open chest wall repair using 
      multiple metallic struts. Rapid recovery ensued, despite a perforated duodenal 
      ulcer on postoperative day 1. Benefits of open fixation of severe flail chest are 
      clearly demonstrated and should be considered instead of prolonged ventilation or 
      supportive care alone for select patients.
