TI  - Non-union of fractures of the sternum.
PG  - 1091-3
AB  - Injuries to the sternum and thoracic cage are relatively frequent in this age of 
      motor-vehicle accidents, high-speed sports activities, and industrial injuries, 
      yet non-union of a fracture of the sternum is exceptionally rare. Sternotomy is 
      commonly performed in cardiothoracic surgery, and the sternum is usually divided 
      vertically or transversely, but non-union of the sternal cut is rare. Fracture of 
      the sternum in a child is especially rare.
